Shoot, I meant to include this on a separate pull request but it looks like I've accidentally included a fix for the `hse_field.py` cookbook recipe for this PR.  Rather than declining a bunch of PRs I'm just going to leave this be since they're at least tangentially related.

@MatthewTurk this includes a possibly dubious fix for smoothed covering grids.  Would love it if you could take a look at [9acc670](https://bitbucket.org/ngoldbaum/yt/commits/9acc67029bc740e0b81dfa6accbd6648da7b49d6).

This also implements the `flat` property for `YTArray`, which I've shamelessly [adapted from astropy](https://github.com/astropy/astropy/pull/2251).
